{"title_page": "2020 Cincinnati Bearcats football team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n| year = 2020\n| team = Cincinnati Bearcats\n| sport= football\n| logo = Cincinnati University Bearcats textlogo.svg\n| logo_size = 200\n| logo_alt = \n| image = \n| image_size =\n| image_alt = \n| conference= American Athletic Conference\n| division = \n| short_conf= The American\n| CFPRank = \n| CoachRank = \n| APRank = \n| record = \n| conf_record = \n| head_coach = [[Luke Fickell]]\n| hc_year = 4th\n| off_coach = [[Mike Denbrock]]\n| oc_year = 4th\n| def_coach = [[Marcus Freeman (linebacker)|Marcus Freeman]]\n| dc_year = 4th\n| off_scheme = \n| def_scheme = \n| stadium = [[Nippert Stadium]]<br />(Capacity: 40,000)\n| champion = \n| conf_champ = \n| conf_champ_result = \n| bowl=\n| bowl_result= \n}}\n{{2020 American Athletic Conference football standings}}\nThe '''2020 Cincinnati Bearcats football team''' will represent the [[University of Cincinnati]] in the [[2020 NCAA Division I FBS football season]]. The Bearcats will play their home games at [[Nippert Stadium]] and compete as members of the [[American Athletic Conference]]. They will be led by fourth-year head coach [[Luke Fickell]].\n\n== Previous season ==\nIn 2019, the Bearcats finished with a 11\u20133 (7\u20131 AAC) record, and won the [[2020 Birmingham Bowl|Birmingham Bowl]] against [[2019 Boston College Eagles football team|Boston College]]. The 2019 season was the second straight 11-win season for the Bearcats, and fourth such season in program history.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ridder, No. 23 Cincinnati romp over Boston College, 38-6 |url=https://www.espn.com/college-football/recap?gameId=401135290 |website=ESPN.com |publisher=Associated Press |accessdate=3 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nRunning back [[Michael Warren II]] would depart early for the [[2020 NFL draft]].\n\n==Recruits==\n\n{{College Athlete Recruit Start|40=no|collapse=yes|year=2020}}\n{{College