{"title_page": "Paul Wheaton", "text_new": "'''Paul Wheaton''' is a contemporary [[permaculture]] [[theorist]],<ref name=\"eugenedailynews\">Stollar, R.L. [http://eugenedailynews.com/2012/08/26/paul-wheaton-and-permaculture-to-visit-lane-county/ \u201cPaul Wheaton and Permaculture\u201d] Eugene Daily News. Retrieved January 4th 2013.</ref><ref name=\"missoulanews.bigskypress\">Fredrickson, Erika. [http://missoulanews.bigskypress.com/missoula/grow-wild/Content?oid=1669018 \"Grow Wild\" {{dead link|date=March 2018}}] Missoula Independent. Retrieved January 4th, 2013.</ref> master [[gardener]],<ref name=\"missoulanews.bigskypress\" /> [[software]] [[engineer]],<ref name=\"eugenedailynews\" /><ref name=\"missoulanews.bigskypress\" /><ref name=\"santamariatimes\">Bushman, Margie. [http://santamariatimes.com/calendar/community/integrating-animals-in-permaculture-systems-with-paul-wheaton/event_851b448a-ed33-11e1-b2b1-bb2891e34df9.html \"Integrating Animals in Permaculture Systems with Paul Wheaton\"] Santa Maria Times. Retrieved January 4th, 2013.</ref> and disciple of natural agriculturist [[Sepp Holzer]].<ref name=\"missoulanews.bigskypress\" /> [[Geoff Lawton]] has called Paul Wheaton \"The Duke of Permaculture\" for being known as the founder<ref name=\"eugenedailynews\" /><ref name=\"missoulanews.bigskypress\" /><ref name=\"missoulian\">Nickell, Joe. [http://missoulian.com/news/local/missoula-man-says-compact-fluorescent-light-bulbs-not-a-bright/article_127ed1d4-0da1-11e1-9dd3-001cc4c03286.html \"Missoula man says compact fluorescent light bulbs not a bright idea\"] Missoulian.com. Retrieved January 4th, 2013.</ref> of related website forums, articles, videos and podcasts such as [https://permies.com/ Permies.com], which is believed to be the largest website devoted to [[permaculture]].<ref name=\"missoulanews.bigskypress\" />\n\nWheaton generously shares his knowledge and has over 84,000 subscribers to his [[YouTube (channel)|YouTube channel]]. Video topics include permaculture, natural building, alternative energy, [[Rocket mass heater|rocket mass heaters]], [[homesteading]], [[frugality]], raising chickens, [[wildcrafting]] (especially nettles), [[aquaculture]], Sepp Holzer, bees, trees, paddock shift systems, and [[Missoula, Montana]].<ref>https://www.youtube.com/user/paulwheaton12/about</ref>\n==Early career==\nBorn in [[Moscow, Idaho]], Wheaton spent time growing up in Northeastern Oregon, and has also lived in Missoula, Montana.\n\nHe began his career as a [[software]] [[engineer]] and continues to lend his knowledge and expertise to those needing help with software or [[Computer programming|programming]]. In the early 90s, Wheaton created a terminal emulator called Bananacom<ref>[http://www.coderanch.com/t/589650/md/BananaCom-DOS-terminal-software Bananacom]</ref> which ended up being one of the more popular pieces of its kind in the 90s because of its simple usability.<ref>Matthews, Noah. \"Bananacom Gets Modem Up, Running\". ''The Billings Gazette''. November 19, 1996.</ref><ref>\"Tallying the Banana\". BBS Magazine. February 1996.</ref><ref>Online Access Magazine, March 1995.</ref><ref>Bechtold, Alan. \"Go Bananas\". Band Street.</ref>\n\nIn 1998 he created a website for Java programming called Java Ranch, which was a massive hit. Now called Code Ranch, the site still exists. 30 volunteers help keep it running. Technology has always been one of  Wheaton's main interests, and he has many projects underway.<ref name=\"eugenedailynews\" /> Before creating permies.com, he was the primary architect of the ground system software for the spacecraft that takes pictures for Google Earth.<ref>Pavelich, Riley. \"Sustainably slacking, Paul Wheaton, the bad boy of permaculture\". Montana Kaimin. 28 February 2013. Web.</ref><ref>Wheaton, Paul. [http://www.javaranch.com/paul-wheaton.jsp \"Paul Wheaton - evil tyrant of JavaRanch\"], Java Ranch</ref>\n\n==Recent projects==\nIn the spring of 2012, Katharina Hirsch brought Sepp Holzer to the US to restore the wetlands and create a large permaculture site on her land in [[Dayton, Montana]]. Paul Wheaton attended the seminar.<ref name=\"theregularjoe\">Bleth, Ariel. [https://fbcdn-sphotos-e-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-frc1/s720x720/578308_399173623457258_519465535_n.jpg The Regular Joe] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502001825/https://fbcdn-sphotos-e-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-frc1/s720x720/578308_399173623457258_519465535_n.jpg |date=2014-05-02 }} (broken link). Retrieved January 4th, 2013.</ref> Since then, Permies.com has attracted notable personalities such as [[Geoff Lawton]] and [[Toby Hemenway]], [[rocket mass heater]] developers [[Ernie and Erica Wisner]], medical [[herbalist]] Michael Pilarski, and others who explore a wide range of eclectic permaculture topics.\n\nPaul Wheaton is the author of \"Building a Better World in Your Backyard, instead of being angry at the bad guys\"<ref>https://www.amazon.com/Building-Better-World-Your-Backyard/dp/1999171403</ref>. He is also the author of many [[article (publishing)|article]]s, both on his richsoil.com website, as well as major publications.  He produces audio [[interview]]s with leading figures in the permaculture movement and [[education]]al podcasts<ref>http://www.permies.com/forums/f-88/permaculture-podcast</ref> on permaculture. Since 2008, he has posted instructional permaculture videos on [[YouTube]], discussing topics like [[organic horticulture]], [[rocket mass heater]]s,[[natural building]] and colony collapse disorder. His videos also include interviews with Sepp Holzer and other leaders of the permaculture field. In 2011, \u201cPermaculture author Paul Wheaton demonstrate[d] how hand washing a standard sized load of dishes can only use around a gallon of water. In comparison, a standard dishwasher uses 15 gallons of water per load and energy-efficient dishwasher use around 9 gallons per load.\u201d<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://lifehacker.com/washing-dishes-by-hand-can-use-less-water-than-a-dishwa-5824344|title=Washing Dishes by Hand Can Use Less Water Than a Dishwasher|website=Lifehacker|language=en-us|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref> \n\nWheaton also set up an experiment to demonstrate how [[Compact fluorescent lamp|compact fluorescent lamps]] (CFL bulbs) are not better than [[Incandescent light bulb|incandescent light bulbs]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/paulwheaton/farmer-laboratory-light-bulbs-at-30-seconds|title=farmer laboratory: light bulbs at 30 seconds|website=Kickstarter|language=en|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref> \n\nAs of April 1st, 2020, Wheaton's YouTube videos had been viewed over 24 million times, and his channel had over 84,000 subscribers.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/user/paulwheaton12</ref>\n\nYou can find more of [https://permies.com/w/stuff Paul Wheaton's Permaculture and Homesteading stuff by clicking here]  <ref>https://permies.com/w/stuff</ref>\n\n==Films Paul Wheaton Helped Develop==\n\n2012 -- [http://www.woodburningstoves2.com/  Woodburning Stoves 2.0.] <ref>http://www.woodburningstoves2.com/</ref> You can visit the [[Kickstarter]] at [https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/paulwheaton/wood-burning-stoves-20-the-dvds?ref=profile_created Wood Burning Stoves 2.0] <ref>https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/paulwheaton/wood-burning-stoves-20-the-dvds?ref=profile_created</ref>\n\n2014 -- [https://richsoil.com/wd-gardening.jsp World Domination Gardening.] <ref>https://richsoil.com/wd-gardening.jsp</ref>  You can visit the [[Kickstarter]] at * [https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/paulwheaton/permaculture-earthworks-and-hugelkultur-garden-3-d World Domination Gardening]  <ref>https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/paulwheaton/permaculture-earthworks-and-hugelkultur-garden-3-d</ref>\n\n2016 -- [https://richsoil.com/wood-heat.jsp Better Wood Heat: DIY Rocket Mass Heaters.]<ref>https://richsoil.com/wood-heat.jsp</ref> You can visit the [[Kickstarter]] at [https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/paulwheaton/rocket-mass-heaters-4-dvd-set?ref=profile_created Kickstarter for Better Wood Heat] <ref>https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/paulwheaton/rocket-mass-heaters-4-dvd-set?ref=profile_created</ref>\n\n2019 -- [https://permies.com/t/rocket-ovens Rocket Oven: More than a Wood Fired Pizza Oven DVD.]<ref>https://permies.com/t/rocket-ovens</ref> You can visit the [[Kickstarter]] at [https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/paulwheaton/rocket-ovens-feature-length-documentary?ref=profile_created Rocket Ovens: More than a Wood Fired Pizza Oven DVD]<ref>https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/paulwheaton/rocket-ovens-feature-length-documentary?ref=profile_created</ref>\n==See also==\n* [[Ralph Borsodi]]\n* [[Food Not Lawns]]\n* [[David Holmgren]]\n* [[Hugelkultur]]\n* [[Bill Mollison]]\n* [[Natural farming]]\n* [[Scott and Helen Nearing]]\n* [[Mike Oehler]]\n* [[Sepp Holzer]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.permies.com Permies: permaculture website and forum]\n* [http://richsoil.com/ Wheaton's blog]\n* [https://wheaton-labs.com Paul Wheaton's page for events at his property, \"Wheaton Labs\"]\n* [https://www.amazon.com/Building-Better-World-Your-Backyard/dp/1999171403 \"Building a Better World in Your Backyard, instead of being angry at the bad guys\" book on Amazon]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wheaton, Paul}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American gardeners]]\n[[Category:Permaculturalists]]\n[[Category:Sustainability advocates]]\n[[Category:American software engineers]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "'''Paul Wheaton''' is a contemporary [[permaculture]] [[theorist]],<ref name=\"eugenedailynews\">Stollar, R.L. [http://eugenedailynews.com/2012/08/26/paul-wheaton-and-permaculture-to-visit-lane-county/ \u201cPaul Wheaton and Permaculture\u201d] Eugene Daily News. Retrieved January 4th 2013.</ref><ref name=\"missoulanews.bigskypress\">Fredrickson, Erika. [http://missoulanews.bigskypress.com/missoula/grow-wild/Content?oid=1669018 \"Grow Wild\" {{dead link|date=March 2018}}] Missoula Independent. Retrieved January 4th, 2013.</ref> master [[gardener]],<ref name=\"missoulanews.bigskypress\" /> [[software]] [[engineer]],<ref name=\"eugenedailynews\" /><ref name=\"missoulanews.bigskypress\" /><ref name=\"santamariatimes\">Bushman, Margie. [http://santamariatimes.com/calendar/community/integrating-animals-in-permaculture-systems-with-paul-wheaton/event_851b448a-ed33-11e1-b2b1-bb2891e34df9.html \"Integrating Animals in Permaculture Systems with Paul Wheaton\"] Santa Maria Times. Retrieved January 4th, 2013.</ref> and disciple of natural agriculturist [[Sepp Holzer]].<ref name=\"missoulanews.bigskypress\" /> [[Geoff Lawton]] has called Paul Wheaton \"The Duke of Permaculture\" for being known as the founder<ref name=\"eugenedailynews\" /><ref name=\"missoulanews.bigskypress\" /><ref name=\"missoulian\">Nickell, Joe. [http://missoulian.com/news/local/missoula-man-says-compact-fluorescent-light-bulbs-not-a-bright/article_127ed1d4-0da1-11e1-9dd3-001cc4c03286.html \"Missoula man says compact fluorescent light bulbs not a bright idea\"] Missoulian.com. Retrieved January 4th, 2013.</ref> of related website forums, articles, videos and podcasts such as [https://permies.com/ Permies.com], which is believed to be the largest website devoted to [[permaculture]].<ref name=\"missoulanews.bigskypress\" />\n\nWheaton generously shares his knowledge and has over 84,000 subscribers to his [[YouTube (channel)|YouTube channel]]. Video topics include permaculture, natural building, alternative energy, [[Rocket mass heater|rocket mass heaters]], [[homesteading]], [[frugality]], raising chickens, [[wildcrafting]] (especially nettles), [[aquaculture]], Sepp Holzer, bees, trees, paddock shift systems, and [[Missoula, Montana]].<ref>https://www.youtube.com/user/paulwheaton12/about</ref>\n==Early career==\nBorn in Moscow, Idaho, Wheaton spent time growing up in Northeastern